==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cohabitant
<hw>Co*hab"it*ant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>cohabitans</ets>, p. pr.]</ety> <def>One who dwells with another,
or in the same place or country.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No small number of the Danes became peaceable
<qex>cohabitants</qex> with the Saxons in England.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Raleigh.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 276 --></p>

<p><ent>Cohabitation</ent>⟦br⟧
